75
00:03:56.220 --> 00:03:59.840
So noting that the policy of the bill is to make the military justice system easier

76
00:03:59.880 --> 00:04:03.820
to navigate and to administer to better enable command to focus

77
00:04:03.860 --> 00:04:07.480
on operational outputs. I'd also like the bill to clarify which

78
00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:10.930
orders issued by the Chief of Defense Force, CDF, are

79
00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:14.600
legislative and which are not. Defense Force orders issued by

80
00:04:14.660 --> 00:04:18.570
CDF are a vital instrument for command and control of the armed forces.

81
00:04:19.161 --> 00:04:23.080
All Defense Force orders are currently deemed to be secondary legislation.

82
00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:26.750
Despite this, the vast majority of Defense Force orders are administrative

83
00:04:27.040 --> 00:04:30.860
rather than legislative in nature, setting policy on matters as varied

84
00:04:30.960 --> 00:04:34.800
as conditions of service for members of the armed forces, intelligence and

85
00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:38.560
security, health and safety, operations and planning, healthcare, and ceremonial

86
00:04:38.600 --> 00:04:42.540
matters. The bill could clarify that Defense Force orders are those orders

87
00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.080
that are administrative rather than legislative

88
00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:49.540
in nature, and creating defense rules as

89
00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.700
a new category of orders for those that have legislative effect.

90
00:04:53.260 --> 00:04:57.240
Orders issued by CDF that impact on the operation of the military justice system

91
00:04:57.340 --> 00:04:59.380
would, of course, be legislative statement.

92
00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:03.700
Excuse me, would of course be legislative and would have the status of new defense

93
00:05:03.740 --> 00:05:04.020
rules.

94
00:05:04.940 --> 00:05:08.360
These could include, for example, the orders currently provided for in the bill to

95
00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:12.320
designate offenses that may be dealt with under the minor disciplinary sanctions

96
00:05:12.420 --> 00:05:15.960
system and other orders already provided for in the AFDA.

97
00:05:16.410 --> 00:05:20.200
As an important safeguard, I propose that the new defense rules would be subject to

98
00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:23.840
the scrutiny of the Regulations Review Committee in the same way as other secondary

99
00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:24.400
legislation.

100
00:05:25.440 --> 00:05:28.660
In conclusion, Mr. Chair, the amendments in the bill are designed to be compliant

101
00:05:28.700 --> 00:05:32.440
with the New Zealand Bill of Rights Act, and it's essential, of course, that the

102
00:05:32.480 --> 00:05:35.040
military justice system is fit for purpose.

103
00:05:35.240 --> 00:05:38.880
These things are not mutually exclusive in my view, and therefore, I conclude that

104
00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:42.539
I believe that reforms will make the system more efficient, streamlined, and fair.

105
00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:46.420
So to you, Mr. Chair, obviously happy to take any questions or commentary that you

106
00:05:46.460 --> 00:05:47.360
and all the committee may have.

