00:12:29.044 --> 00:12:29.544
cause.

247
00:12:30.664 --> 00:12:32.344
The question underneath.

248
00:12:33.904 --> 00:12:36.664
Not surprisingly, the forces are not alone in grappling

249
00:12:37.684 --> 00:12:41.544
with this problem. It is a problem with society at large.

250
00:12:42.364 --> 00:12:44.824
One of the fundamental problems in our society

251
00:12:46.344 --> 00:12:49.484
is that we think women are special and men are bad.

252
00:12:50.744 --> 00:12:54.004
So in the West, some groups in the past have promoted the idea of

253
00:12:54.064 --> 00:12:57.424
patriarchy and the idea of dominance by men.

254
00:12:58.204 --> 00:13:01.584
Conversely, when women are the boss, this means success,

255
00:13:02.124 --> 00:13:04.024
and men are always the problem.

256
00:13:05.324 --> 00:13:08.754
However, today, with women getting the vote and entering the workforce, we still

257
00:13:08.784 --> 00:13:10.044
have men harming women.

258
00:13:11.164 --> 00:13:13.524
Why? What is driving this?

259
00:13:14.984 --> 00:13:18.604
The question is: why do men lose it?

260
00:13:19.364 --> 00:13:23.264
Do they feel that the work being done to improve equality

261
00:13:23.364 --> 00:13:25.024
has not been a success or having

262
00:13:26.244 --> 00:13:29.444
led to outcomes that they now feel disadvantaged?

263
00:13:30.544 --> 00:13:34.004
In this thought, I want you to avoid making it worse.

264
00:13:34.764 --> 00:13:38.524
So given we've done our best to address wrongs, have we

265
00:13:38.604 --> 00:13:40.104
made some things worse?

266
00:13:41.464 --> 00:13:45.444
We've made men to believe that women have

267
00:13:45.484 --> 00:13:49.384
become privileged and that they are now seen as inferior.

268
00:13:51.084 --> 00:13:53.424
So they've gone and decided to treat them like dirt.

269
00:13:54.284 --> 00:13:55.284
Has this happened?

270
00:13:56.184 --> 00:13:58.744
If the answer is yes, how did it happen?

271
00:14:00.084 --> 00:14:04.064
If we push men in 2026 and blame them, and we

272
00:14:04.084 --> 00:14:08.004
appear to reward women and punish them, are

273
00:14:08.064 --> 00:14:12.044
we inadvertently making it worse by doing what we believe is right?

274
00:14:13.484 --> 00:14:17.464
Protecting women is a good thing I want to keep, but

275
00:14:17.564 --> 00:14:20.934
how to feed it without producing an unintended outcome.

276
00:14:21.914 --> 00:14:25.794
We have been building more prisons in the belief that we can fix crime,

277
00:14:26.184 --> 00:14:27.384
and yet we have more crime.

278
00:14:28.504 --> 00:14:32.284
Something tells me that a belief is wrong if my

279
00:14:32.294 --> 00:14:33.544
solution is not working.

280
00:14:35.364 --> 00:14:37.964
This part, we tell everyone that they are equal.

281
00:14:38.504 --> 00:14:42.444
We are, in fact, maybe paradoxically producing the

282
00:14:42.804 --> 00:14:44.584
very thing we are trying to prevent.

283
00:14:46.564 --> 00:14:50.524
Instead of arguing for greater transparency for offenders

284
00:14:50.544 --> 00:14:54.064
being caught and punished, I want to ask: what is the cause?

285
00:14:54.444 --> 00:14:58.044
What is the cause? The solution is to have deeper

286
00:14:58.104 --> 00:15:00.684
thought and less shallow analysis.

287
00:15:04.244 --> 00:15:07.824
All right. Thank you very much, Mr. Marshall. We have time for one question. Mr.

288
00:15:07.844 --> 00:15:08.364
Costley.

289
00:15:08.804 --> 00:15:12.584
Thank you. I just want to be really clear that if anyone is offending in this way,

290
00:15:13.384 --> 00:15:17.294
particularly in your example against women, it is not the fault of a woman, and

291
00:15:17.324 --> 00:15:19.304
I'm not looking for a way to justify that behavior.

292
00:15:19.364 --> 00:15:21.784
I don't think that's ever okay, and I want to be very clear about that.

293
00:15:22.704 --> 00:15:23.824
You also made the point that

294
00:15:24.824 --> 00:15:26.744
putting people in prison maybe doesn't solve it.

295
00:15:26.884 --> 00:15:27.044
But

296
00:15:28.204 --> 00:15:31.084
how would you respond then to the fact that since this government's been in for two

297
00:15:31.104 --> 00:15:34.684
and a half years, toughened up laws, brought back three strikes, gone really hard

298
00:15:34.724 --> 00:15:36.004
on serious and violent offending.

299
00:15:36.124 --> 00:15:39.544
Last year alone, there were 49,000 less victims than the year before.

300
00:15:40.384 --> 00:15:43.304
Yes, there are more people in prison, but consequence has seen far less

301
00:15:43.344 --> 00:15:45.444
victimization. Isn't that a good thing?

302
00:15:46.804 --> 00:15:47.704
Yeah, it is.

303
00:15:49.044 --> 00:15:49.363
I

304
00:15:50.924 --> 00:15:54.243
guess if you looked at a

305
00:15:57.244 --> 00:16:01.164
male and a sexual offender, where did he

306
00:16:02.364 --> 00:16:06.324
lose it? And that's what we're not asking here.

307
00:16:06.724 --> 00:16:10.204
We can go and say, "Well, we have more success because

308
00:16:10.964 --> 00:16:14.324
look at us, we've fixed the force. We've put all these people

309
00:16:15.204 --> 00:16:17.604
aside." But that doesn't

310
00:16:17.683 --> 00:16:20.964
necessarily mean success.

311
00:16:21.784 --> 00:16:22.084
We've...

312
00:16:22.984 --> 00:16:23.834
Okay. Thank you.

313
00:16:23.834 --> 00:16:26.584
All right. Thank you very much for your perspectives. Chair.

314
00:16:28.804 --> 00:16:31.044
Okay. Next up, we have Graeme Edgeler.

315
00:16:35.244 --> 00:16:36.224
Good afternoon, Mr. Edgeler.

316
00:16:36.264 --> 00:16:37.044
Thank you for having me.

317
00:16:37.104 --> 00:16:40.004
Thank you for joining us. Thank you for your time making your written submission

318
00:16:40.124 --> 00:16:43.584
and indeed coming in today. Our members have all had a chance to read that.

319
00:16:43.884 --> 00:16:46.544
So we welcome your comments on that.

320
00:16:46.824 --> 00:16:49.854
We have 10 minutes set down for that today, and I'm sure there'll be some

321
00:16:49.924 --> 00:16:50.464
questions.

322
00:16:50.824 --> 00:16:54.344
Thank you. It's good. I think I'm finally in front of the

323
00:16:54.684 --> 00:16:58.604
right select committee. Mr. Costley has mentioned three strikes, and I

324
00:16:58.644 --> 00:17:02.404
think the point I make about three strikes in my submission is something

325
00:17:02.464 --> 00:17:05.785
I've mentioned definitely once and I think twice in various submissions for three

326
00:17:05.884 --> 00:17:09.444
strikes to the Justice Committee about, oh, have you considered whether people

327
00:17:09.484 --> 00:17:12.704
convicted of strike offenses at court-martial should be covered by three strikes?

328
00:17:12.785 --> 00:17:15.535
And the response I got at that time and the advice was,

329
00:17:16.364 --> 00:17:16.585
"That's

330
00:17:17.504 --> 00:17:19.585
not a matter for the Ministry of Justice to deal with.

331
00:17:19.594 --> 00:17:22.644
That's a matter for someone else." And so I think I have the right committee to

332
00:17:22.684 --> 00:17:26.204
look at that. My general view is I oppose three

333
00:17:26.264 --> 00:17:30.134
strikes. The current version of three strikes you have is actually a

334
00:17:30.144 --> 00:17:33.824
pretty good one. If you're going to have one that has the protections in

335
00:17:33.864 --> 00:17:36.864
place that you want it to have, that's a matter for someone else.

336
00:17:36.884 --> 00:17:40.064
But if you are to have one, then I think it is important that it does apply to

337
00:17:40.084 --> 00:17:42.584
everyone who gets that level of conviction.

338
00:17:42.604 --> 00:17:42.664
Mm-hmm.

339
00:17:43.444 --> 00:17:46.874
And certainly, there have been rape

340
00:17:47.044 --> 00:17:50.684
prosecutions at court-martial. There have certainly been a number of rape

341
00:17:50.744 --> 00:17:51.634
conv... Oh, sorry, not rape.

342
00:17:52.504 --> 00:17:55.224
Indecent assault convictions at court-martial as well.

343
00:17:55.644 --> 00:17:59.322
And in none of those cases-If three strikes had applied, would

344
00:17:59.712 --> 00:18:02.592
a first strike have happened? And so if that person

345
00:18:03.532 --> 00:18:06.792
leaves the military at that point, goes on to the

346
00:18:07.292 --> 00:18:10.312
civilian population, and gets charged again, they would not have a strike history.

347
00:18:11.332 --> 00:18:13.812
And if you are to have a strike law,

348
00:18:14.612 --> 00:18:18.432
it should apply, I think, where wherever the conviction is, whether it's in a civil

349
00:18:18.492 --> 00:18:20.472
court or a military court. And so,

350
00:18:22.032 --> 00:18:25.172
I think that should be something that should be looked at seriously as,

351
00:18:26.212 --> 00:18:28.432
if we're going to have this, then it should apply consistently.

352
00:18:28.912 --> 00:18:32.192
I have a few other points, sort of related points about sort of criminal conviction

353
00:18:32.252 --> 00:18:32.562
history,

354
00:18:33.392 --> 00:18:35.312
and things like that, possibly slightly less important.

355
00:18:35.892 --> 00:18:39.722
But, again, that is something that I've noti-- has come up a few times in the

356
00:18:39.792 --> 00:18:42.792
past. There's just a news article about someone, and someone wasn't aware that this

357
00:18:42.812 --> 00:18:46.482
person had been convicted of this, because if you go to the Ministry of Justice and

358
00:18:46.532 --> 00:18:50.512
ask for a conviction history, if someone has a conviction for even something

359
00:18:50.552 --> 00:18:53.962
as serious as rape in the military, and I'm not sure there has been, but there

360
00:18:54.032 --> 00:18:57.672
certainly have been in decent assault, that will not show up on a Ministry of

361
00:18:57.732 --> 00:18:58.932
Justice conviction history.

362
00:18:59.012 --> 00:18:59.422
Mm-hmm.

363
00:18:59.852 --> 00:19:03.472
If someone's doing a full sort of review of someone, do police

364
00:19:03.552 --> 00:19:06.922
assessment, security review, then they'll get a copy of their military service

365
00:19:06.972 --> 00:19:08.432
history or something like that, and they'll find out.

366
00:19:08.452 --> 00:19:12.192
But if you're a private organization where what you do, your due

367
00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:16.212
diligence in advance is, "Can we have a copy of your conviction history?" You will

368
00:19:16.292 --> 00:19:19.712
not get a conviction in the military. And most of the time that will make sense.

369
00:19:20.132 --> 00:19:22.772
Someone was late to parade, that type of thing.

370
00:19:23.292 --> 00:19:24.532
The military justice system

371
00:19:25.452 --> 00:19:28.772
is, to an extent, what would be in any other circumstance, the large

372
00:19:29.272 --> 00:19:32.012
uses of it are employment matters. This person was late today.

373
00:19:32.912 --> 00:19:35.012
In the military, that can result in a trial.

374
00:19:35.352 --> 00:19:37.772
Somewhere else, it would just be a disciplinary meeting with your manager or

375
00:19:37.792 --> 00:19:39.452
something like that. And so it makes sense.

376
00:19:39.532 --> 00:19:43.052
But when you're talking about particularly the Section 74-1 offenses, that is, this

377
00:19:43.092 --> 00:19:46.222
is an offense against New Zealand's criminal law that applies to everyone,

378
00:19:47.252 --> 00:19:50.712
then I think probably the same rule should apply.

379
00:19:50.772 --> 00:19:54.751
The other matter I'll speak to now briefly is name suppression.

380
00:19:55.652 --> 00:19:55.952
I think

381
00:19:56.792 --> 00:19:59.972
if you are going to have name suppression that can be ordered by non-judges, then

382
00:19:59.992 --> 00:20:02.732
it makes sense that there is the possibility for an appeal.

383
00:20:03.652 --> 00:20:05.242
The thing I would suggest for you is,

384
00:20:06.052 --> 00:20:09.852
get some advice on how often... There have been name suppressions by

385
00:20:09.892 --> 00:20:13.232
disciplinary officers over the last few years, one particularly famous one.

386
00:20:13.512 --> 00:20:14.852
I don't know if there have been any others.

387
00:20:14.892 --> 00:20:16.452
I suspect they're not needed all that often.

388
00:20:16.552 --> 00:20:19.692
But if there aren't that many, and my suspicion is there aren't,

389
00:20:20.392 --> 00:20:24.032
then this is probably something that you could just have judges involved in.

390
00:20:25.112 --> 00:20:28.832
The types of things that, name suppression will sometimes be appropriate.

391
00:20:29.392 --> 00:20:32.012
Often you won't need it in the military, because someone can say, "Don't say

392
00:20:32.052 --> 00:20:35.272
anything," and military people are used to following orders.

393
00:20:35.572 --> 00:20:37.912
And so you might not need a suppression order, and you're like, if the information

394
00:20:37.932 --> 00:20:39.632
doesn't get out, then it doesn't matter who knows about it.

395
00:20:40.532 --> 00:20:44.212
But for the particularly serious ones, if there is a case like the case we know of

396
00:20:44.232 --> 00:20:47.101
from a few years back, and there might be other ones that I, as a sort of member of

397
00:20:47.132 --> 00:20:47.952
the public, don't know about.

398
00:20:48.892 --> 00:20:52.712
Just get some advice on, there have been or there's been the suggestion

399
00:20:52.752 --> 00:20:56.652
that suppression power already exists, and it has been exercised.

400
00:20:57.472 --> 00:21:01.312
My suspicion is it hasn't been exercised very much, and so the few instances where

401
00:21:01.352 --> 00:21:04.922
it is needed, you probably could just go to a judge and get the order, and that

402
00:21:04.932 --> 00:21:08.432
would sort of, the types of things that you want in place when

403
00:21:08.972 --> 00:21:11.872
someone is ordering journalists not to publish something.

404
00:21:12.532 --> 00:21:15.932
Someone who is trained at balancing that will be a

405
00:21:16.432 --> 00:21:19.761
judge of court-martial and not necessarily someone's commanding officer who will

406
00:21:20.212 --> 00:21:23.212
generally have some legal advice but will not be legally trained.

407
00:21:23.632 --> 00:21:26.272
Happy to take questions on that or any other aspect of my submission.

408
00:21:26.712 --> 00:21:29.012
Yeah, excellent. Hey, thanks so much for that.

409
00:21:29.432 --> 00:21:32.372
Really appreciate that insight into a range of different areas.

410
00:21:33.092 --> 00:21:33.182
Mm-hmm.

411
00:21:33.202 --> 00:21:35.772
And I think you raised some really valid concerns there.

412
00:21:35.932 --> 00:21:39.862
Just on that last one, I'm interested in your assessment and obviously, you

413
00:21:39.892 --> 00:21:43.412
note that they have a good understanding of the need for suppression, but they

414
00:21:43.452 --> 00:21:47.152
don't necessarily have a good understanding of the military reason around why it

415
00:21:47.192 --> 00:21:49.472
might be important. Do you see a potential issue with that?

416
00:21:50.032 --> 00:21:50.152
Uh-

417
00:21:50.212 --> 00:21:51.552
You're proposing it goes to judges.

418
00:21:51.832 --> 00:21:54.632
Well, it would be judges of court-martial.

